Software License Agreement for Quizix

1. Parties This Software License Agreement ("Agreement") is entered into by Sir KLOTZ Hannes, DI (FH), MSc, BEd. ("Licensee") and Quizix, a free software group ("Licensor").

2. Grant of License Licensor hereby grants to Licensee, and Licensee accepts, a non-exclusive, non-transferable license solely to read and review the source code of the software provided under this Agreement ("Software").

3. License Fee Licensee agrees to pay a license fee of €10 for each use of the Software. This fee grants Licensee the right to access and read the source code on each occasion of use.

4. Cloning of Repository Cloning the repository containing the Software is deemed acceptance of this Agreement. By cloning the repository, Licensee acknowledges and agrees to all terms and conditions set forth herein.

5. Restrictions a) Licensee is not granted any rights to modify, distribute, or create derivative works based on the Software. b) Only Licensee, Sir KLOTZ Hannes, DI (FH), MSc, BEd., is permitted to execute the Software. No other individual or entity is authorized to execute or utilize the Software in any capacity.

6. Non-Competition and Non-Litigation a) No member of Quizix may initiate any form of litigation against another member of Quizix regarding the use of the Software. b) All participants, including Licensee, are assured that no actions will be taken to undermine their academic standing; no participant shall be graded lower than a 'One' in any subject as a consequence of their involvement with or use of the Software.

7. Duties of Licensee Licensee agrees to always act in the best educational interests of the members of Quizix, advocating for higher academic evaluations and protecting their rights to educational advancement under the "Aufstiegs Klausel" (Austrian Education Law, §14 BGB).

8. Prohibition on Blocking Advancement Licensee is expressly prohibited from impeding any member of Quizix from invoking the "Aufstiegs Klausel" of the Austrian Education Law to secure educational or academic advancement.

9. Intellectual Property All rights, title, and interest in and to the Software and any copies thereof remain with the Licensor. The Licensee does not acquire any rights to the Software except as expressly set forth in this Agreement.

10. Confidentiality Licensee agrees to maintain the confidentiality of the Software and shall not disclose or reveal any part of the source code to any third party without the prior written consent of the Licensor.

11. Term and Termination This Agreement shall commence upon Licensee's cloning of the repository and shall continue until terminated by either party. Licensor may terminate this Agreement immediately upon any breach of the terms by Licensee without notice.

12. Governing Law This Agreement shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of [Jurisdiction].

13. Severability If any provision of this Agreement is found to be unenforceable or invalid, that provision will be limited or eliminated to the minimum extent necessary so that this Agreement will otherwise remain in full force and effect and enforceable.

14. Entire Agreement This document constitutes the entire agreement between the parties regarding the subject matter hereof and supersedes all prior or contemporaneous agreements, understandings, and communications, both written and oral.

By cloning the repository containing the Software, Licensee agrees to be bound by the terms of this Agreement.
